# Azure Plan

## Status: Draft

## Decisions

### Mode: MODIFY
- Existing codebase will be enhanced with Azure deployment capabilities
- No changes to existing application logic

### Requirements
- Classification: MCP Server (Model Context Protocol)
- Scale: Prototype/Small (under 100 concurrent users)
- Budget: $$ (cost-conscious, use Free/Pay-as-You-Go tier)
- Krit Characteristics: Serverless container deployment

### Tech Stack
- Base: Node.js 20 LTS
- Framework: Express.js (via @modelcontextprotocol/sdk)
- Deployment: Container-based (Azure Container Apps)

### Recipe: AZD (Azure Developer CLI)
- Infrastructure: Bicep templates
- Deployment: azd up command
- Justification: Standard MSFT recommendation, supports all ecosystems

### Architecture
- Service: Azure Container Apps
- Reasoning: Containerized Node.js server, pay-for-what-you-use scaling
- Networking: Public endpoint with API routing

### Infrastructure Resources
- Microsoft.App/containerApps
- Microsoft.App/managedEnvironments
- Microsoft.Network/frontDoors (if CDN needed)
- Microsoft.Storage/storageAccounts (for logs)

### Security
- Authentication: Entra ID (if needed)
- Networking: Private endpoints where possible
- Secrets: Azure Key Vault integration

## Implementation Steps
1. ✅ Analyze codebase and dependencies
2. ⏳ Generate AZD configuration files (azure.yaml)
3. ⏳ Create infrastructure Bicep templates
4. ⏳ Add Docker containerization (Dockerfile)
5. ⏳ Configure application for Azure environment
6. ⏳ Add health checks and monitoring
7. ⏳ Security hardening (RBAC, secrets management)
8. ⏳ Testing and validation

## Next Steps
- Review and approve this plan
- Execute implementation steps
- Run azd up for deployment</content>
